I’m a little late today, even for me, but I got to my mat. During this holiday season I want to say I’m thankful for getting on a yoga journey and brining that practice to my life. I have grown and changed in a lot of ways, many of them indescribable until there is a skill I need, and all of a sudden, I have it. My 4 year old loves doing yoga now too (and is so cute with her tiny mat) and I’m thinking we have the same favorite pose. I’ve introduced a few friends to yoga with Adriene, in hopes that they find as much love for yoga as I have found, and for the benefits that it can bring to one’s life. It is my way of showing love, and giving to others as I feel so much has been given to me. Have a blessed and safe holiday season! Namaste 🙏🏾

Good morning Adriene from Dallas, TX. I got emotional during this practice... I have been doing your practices  for 7 months and it has truly changed my life. Today I had tears streaming while we were doing happy baby. I felt joy at first and I as I felt happy about feeling like a child I realized that there have been moments in my kids life that they were just being joyous kids but because of what I think are societal norms I may have got on to them or been unkind because I discouraged their child like behavior.. I felt sad. I sobbed, shoot I'm still getting misty eyed.. but their childhood is not over, I can promise to make today and every day of the rest of their childhood more joyous and embrace those silly goofy moments even when we are out in public. I'm rambling.. anyway.. I just could go on forever. Thank you for changing my life. You have taught me what progress truly means and you have softened my soul.
Thank you Adriene

Thank you so much for going "do the half plank" to remind me that I don't have to go all out with yoga. Maybe one day I'll get to full plank, but giving a gentle reminder that we can do half plank helps so much. Also, no matter what I do, my lower back right above my hips is always tense and hurts after I get off the mat. I've put a pillow underneath my knees, used a yoga block as my pillow, but nothing was helping until today. When you said to come to any kind of seat at the end, I took a cross legged seat but then took a couple breaths to reach out with both hands in front of me for a gentle back stretch. When the video was over, I sat there with my hands palm up on my knees and bowed my head to my lap, which was also a very nice stretch. Both helped me to come off the mat without my back hurt / clenching and I just thought I would share the love / help. :)
